# Daily Workflow

Every trading day follow this order.

Never skip steps.

Never jump ahead.

---

# STEP 1 — Macro Context (4H)

Determine one of these market states.

### A. Bullish Trend

Requirements

• HH
• HL

Action

Only look for BUYS.

---

### B. Bearish Trend

Requirements

• LH
• LL

Action

Only look for SELLS.

---

### C. Consolidation

Requirements

Price moving sideways.

No clean HH-HL or LH-LL sequence.

Action

Mark:

Range High

Range Low

Premium

Discount

Equilibrium

---

# STEP 2 — Market Condition Rules

## CASE 1

4H Trending

↓

1H Trending Same Direction

Action

Normal trading allowed.

Highest probability.

---

## CASE 2

4H Trending

↓

1H Pullback / Consolidation

Action

Wait.

Do NOT trade inside the pullback.

Wait for:

• Breakout

OR

Price reaches HTF POI.

Then continue.

---

## CASE 3

4H Consolidating

Action

Trade ONLY from:

Range High

OR

Range Low

Never trade Equilibrium.

---

## CASE 4

4H Consolidation

↓

1H Consolidation

Action

NO TRADE.

---

# STEP 3 — Trading Bias (1H)

Questions

Who owns external structure?

Bullish

Bearish

Range

If unsure

NO TRADE.

---

# STEP 4 — Premium / Discount

If Bullish

Only buy Discount.

Never buy Premium.

---

If Bearish

Only sell Premium.

Never sell Discount.

---

If Range

Buy only Discount.

Sell only Premium.

Never trade Equilibrium.

---

# STEP 5 — POI Selection (15M)

Allowed POIs

✅ Fresh Order Block

✅ Fresh Supply Zone

✅ Fresh Demand Zone

✅ Fresh Fair Value Gap

Not Fresh?

Ignore.

Already Mitigated?

Ignore.

Middle of nowhere?

Ignore.

---

# STEP 6 — Wait

Do absolutely nothing until price reaches the POI.

No anticipation.

No guessing.

No limit entries before reaction.

---

# STEP 7 — Reaction (5M)

Once price reaches POI

Observe only.

Do not enter.

---

Need evidence.

Examples

• Strong rejection

• Strong displacement

If nothing happens

NO TRADE.

---

# STEP 8 — Confirmation

Need

✅ Strong Displacement

AND

✅ BOS or MSS

No BOS?

No Trade.

No Displacement?

No Trade.

---

# STEP 9 — Evaluate Retracement

GOOD Retracement

• Slow

• Small candles

• Overlapping candles

• Multiple wicks

• Looks weak

BAD Retracement

• Large opposite candles

• Strong momentum

• Consecutive displacement

• Looks aggressive

Good

↓

Continue.

Bad

↓

No Trade.

---

# STEP 10 — Entry Trigger

Allowed Triggers

• Engulfing candle

OR

• Fresh displacement candle

OR

• BOS after retracement

First trigger

↓

Enter.

No trigger

↓

No Trade.

---

# STEP 11 — Stop Loss

Place SL

Above retracement high

(SELL)

Below retracement low

(BUY)

If SL becomes too large

Skip trade.

Never force it.

---

# STEP 12 — Take Profit

Target

Nearest meaningful liquidity

Examples

• Swing High

• Swing Low

• Equal High

• Equal Low

• PDH

• PDL

Minimum RR

2R

If less than 2R

Skip trade.

---

# Trade Management

Backtesting

Set & Forget.

No partials.

